qupath.ext.py4j.core.QuPathEntryPointAddon
public class QuPathEntryPointAddon extends QuPathEntryPoint
Add methods I found useful to QuPathEntryPoint. It will serve the main entry point of the extension.

    • openImageDataInQuPath

      public static void openImageDataInQuPath(ImageData<BufferedImage> imageData)
      Open image imageData in the current viewer getCurrentViewer() in QuPath. It will become the current image data and can be retrieved by getCurrentImageData().

      If the current project contains imageData, the associated ProjectImageEntry will become the current project entry and can be retrieved by getProjectEntry(). Otherwise, the current project will be closed.

      Parameters:
      imageData - the image to open
      See Also:

    • closeImageDataInQuPath

      public static void closeImageDataInQuPath()
      Close the current image data getCurrentImageData() in QuPath. getCurrentImageData() will return null when this is done.

      The associated project entry will become "inactive". That is, getProjectEntry() will return null.

    • setImageType

      public static void setImageType(ImageData<BufferedImage> imageData) throws IOException
      Set the image type of image data imageData.

      If the image type is not set, it will be estimated.
      If the image type setting is set to PathPrefs.ImageTypeSetting.PROMPT, a prompt will be displayed to set the image type.
      If the image type setting is set to PathPrefs.ImageTypeSetting.AUTO_ESTIMATE, the image type will be automatically set.

      Parameters:
      imageData - the image data to set the image type
      Throws:
      IOException

    • refreshThumbnail

      public static void refreshThumbnail(ProjectImageEntry<BufferedImage> entry, ImageServer<BufferedImage> server) throws IOException
      Refresh entry's thumbnail using server's "computed" thumbnail.

      ProjectImageEntry does not have function like getServer() to retrieve its associated image server. It does provide readImageData() and we are supposed to be able to use ImageData.getServer() to retrieve the associated image server. The problem is that readImageData() is to read the "saved" image data (NOT THE CURRENT IMAGE DATA). That's why we explicitly specify the image server to use to refresh the thumbnail.

      Parameters:
      entry - the image entry to refresh the thumbnail
      server - the image server to get the thumbnail from
      Throws:
      IOException - if an error occurs while getting the thumbnail
      See Also:
      • ProjectCommands.getThumbnailRGB(ImageServer)
      • ProjectImageEntry.setThumbnail(T)
